1–1101 ), son of Tancred, recovered Sicily from the Arabs. His son, also called Roger, ruled Sicily as king, presiding over a court noted for its splendour and patronage of the arts."],"variants":[{"name":"Rodger","meanings":["Variant spelling of   Roger  , in part from the surname derived from the given name in the Middle Ages."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"When Roger d'Aldwark was born about 1235, in Aldwark, North Yorkshire, England, United Kingdom, his father, Galfrid d'Aldwarke, was 43 and his mother, Mrs. Matilda De Aldwarke, was 50. He had at least 1 son and 1 daughter with Joan de Normanville."},"et":{"about 1235–":"umbes 1235–Surnud","1220–Male":"1220–Surnud","1235–Male":"1235–Surnud","1240–1324":"1240–1324","1254–1332":"1254–1332","1276–Female":"1276–Surnud","1193–Male":"1193–Surnud","1187–Female":"1187–Surnud","1324":"1324","1235":"1235","Abt 1276":"umbes 1276","1332":"1332","1254":"1254","1276":"1276","about 1235":"umbes 1235","1187":"1187","1220":"1220","1240":"1240","1193":"1193","Aldwark, North Yorkshire, England, United Kingdom":"Aldwark, North Yorkshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Aldwark, North Ride, Yorkshire, England":"Aldwark, Yorkshire, England","Alderwarke Castle, Alderwarke, Yorkshire, England":"Yorkshire, England"},"fi":{"about 1235–":"noin 1235–Kuollut","1220–Male":"1220–Kuollut","1235–Male":"1235–Kuollut","1240–1324":"1240–1324","1254–1332":"1254–1332","1276–Female":"1276–Kuollut","1193–Male":"1193–Kuollut","1187–Female":"1187–Kuollut","1324":"1324","1235":"1235","Abt 1276":"noin 1276","1332":"1332","1254":"1254","1276":"1276","about 1235":"noin 1235","1187":"1187","1220":"1220","1240":"1240","1193":"1193","Aldwark, North Yorkshire, England, United Kingdom":"Aldwark, North Yorkshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Aldwark, North Ride, Yorkshire, England":"Aldwark, Yorkshire, England","Alderwarke Castle, Alderwarke, Yorkshire, England":"Yorkshire, England"},"fr":{"about 1235–":"environ 1235–Décédé","1220–Male":"1220–Décédé","1235–Male":"1235–